    {
      "directory": ".",
      "description": "# 🔧 Understanding Terraform Init\n\n**What does `terraform init` do?** It prepares your workspace:\n\n- **Downloads providers** (like installing racing car parts)\n- **Initializes modules** (sets up our team and driver modules)\n- **Creates hidden files** for Terraform's internal management\n\n**Let's run it:**\nSelect [this link](command:codetour.sendTextToTerminal?[\"terraform init\"]) to initialize your racing infrastructure workspace.\n\n**What you'll see:**\n- Provider downloads (Okta provider ~50MB)\n- Module initialization messages\n- Success confirmation\n\n**New files created:**\n- `.terraform/` folder (Terraform's workspace data)\n- `.terraform.lock.hcl` (locks provider versions)\n\n**⏰ This takes 10-30 seconds** depending on your connection. Watch for \"Terraform has been successfully initialized!\" ✅"
    },
    {
      "directory": ".",
      "description": "# 📁 Explore What Terraform Init Created\n\n**Let's see the new files that were created!**\n\n**Check your file structure:**\nSelect [this link](command:codetour.sendTextToTerminal?[\"ls -la\"]) to see all files including hidden ones.\n\n**You should now see:**\n- `.terraform/` folder (contains downloaded providers and modules)\n- `.terraform.lock.hcl` (version lock file - keeps your builds consistent)\n- Your existing files (main.tf, variables.tf, etc.)\n\n**VS Code file explorer:** You might see a `.terraform` folder appear in the left sidebar (if you have \"show hidden files\" enabled).\n\n**🎯 Key insight:** Terraform creates a local workspace with everything needed to manage your infrastructure. This is normal and expected! 📂"
    },
    {
      "directory": ".",
      "description": "# 👀 Check Your Okta Dashboard - BEFORE\n\n**IMPORTANT:** Before running any terraform commands, let's see what's currently in your Okta org!\n\n🔍 **Go to your Okta Admin Console and check the Groups page**\n- You should see just \"Everyone\" and maybe a few default groups\n- Note what exists now so you can see the difference after Terraform runs\n\n**🎯 Why check first?**\n- See the \"before\" state\n- Appreciate the changes Terraform will make\n- Troubleshoot if things don't look right later\n\n**Ready to proceed?** Keep that browser tab open - you'll check again after deployment!"
    },
    {
      "directory": ".",
      "description": "# 🔍 Understanding Terraform Plan\n\n**What does `terraform plan` do?** It's your safety check before making changes:\n\n- **Compares** your code to current infrastructure state\n- **Shows** exactly what will be created, modified, or destroyed  \n- **Validates** your configuration without making changes\n- **Estimates** costs and potential issues\n\n**Think of it as:** Race strategy planning before the actual race!\n\n**Let's see your plan:**\nSelect [this link](command:codetour.sendTextToTerminal?[\\\"terraform plan\\\"]) to preview what will be created.\n\n**📋 What to look for:**\n- `+ create` lines show new resources\n- Resource names like `okta_group.racing_teams[\"velocity\"]`\n- Plan summary: \"X to add, Y to change, Z to destroy\"\n\n**⏰ Takes 5-15 seconds** - Terraform is analyzing your configuration!"
    },
    {
      "directory": ".",
      "description": "# 📊 Reading Your Plan Output\n\n**Your plan should show something like:**\n\n```\n# okta_group.racing_teams[\"velocity\"] will be created\n+ resource \"okta_group\" \"racing_teams\" {\n    + description = \"Speed-focused racing team...\"\n    + name        = \"Velocity Racing\"\n    + type        = \"OKTA_GROUP\"\n  }\n```\n\n**Key symbols:**\n- `+` = Will be created\n- `~` = Will be modified \n- `-` = Will be destroyed\n- `#` = Comment explaining the action\n\n**Plan summary shows:** \"4 to add, 0 to change, 0 to destroy\"\n\n**🎯 This means:** Creating 4 new racing teams, no changes to existing resources!\n\n**Ready to proceed?** The plan looks good - let's make it happen! 🏁"
    },
    {
      "directory": ".",
      "description": "# 🚀 Understanding Terraform Apply\n\n**What does `terraform apply` do?** It makes your infrastructure dreams reality:\n\n- **Executes** the plan you just reviewed\n- **Makes API calls** to create/modify/delete resources\n- **Updates state file** to track what exists\n- **Shows progress** as changes happen\n\n**Think of it as:** Actually racing the race after planning the strategy!\n\n**Let's deploy your teams:**\nSelect [this link](command:codetour.sendTextToTerminal?[\\\"terraform apply\\\"]) to create your racing infrastructure!\n\n**💡 Important:** Type `yes` when prompted to confirm\n\n**What you'll see:**\n- Confirmation prompt (safety feature!)\n- Real-time creation progress\n- Success messages for each resource\n- Final summary of changes made\n\n**⏰ Takes 10-30 seconds** - Creating real resources in Okta! 🏗️"
    },
